WADDELL & SONS, Inc., v. PARNELL. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. November 14, 1922.) No. 3797. William R. Watkins, of Wichita Falls, Tex. (Kenneth W. Tapp, of Kansas City, Mo., and Jos. H. Aynesworth, of Wichita Falls, Tex., on the brief), for plaintiff in error. Charles C. McDonald, of Wichita Falls, Tex., for defendant in error.

Before WALKER, BRYAÑ, and KING, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
